{
  "texts": [
    "In the original system, we could only respond suitably to utterances that the system was pre-designed to handle -and we would attempt to respond to unexpected utterances with tips, teaching the user what the system can do (e.g.",
    "\"I'm not sure, but I can help you with directions and menu information.\").",
    "Many of these unexpected utterances can now be handled directly by the LLM.",
    "In-prompt Knowledge Certain LLMs, like ChatGPT and Bard, are regularly asked general knowledge questions and ex-pected to understand chit-chat.",
    "General LLM evaluation has therefore focused on their world knowledge learned at pre-training."
  ]
}